<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2008-01-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Membrane technology could play a part in finding a cure for HIV</TITLE><BODY>Scientists in Australia have completed initial research on specially designed ceramic membranes that have the potential to remove viruses from water, air and blood. They say, as this brief feature shows, that membrane technology could play an important role in saving the lives of millions of people.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>